The paper focuses on a tool for assisting in code review, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The tool leverages content from professional programmer support forums, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques, placing it under the programming languages (cs.PL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of document fingerprinting for comparing source code also falls under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
